{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LzK5xkXRzHTic3FBjXkVEF","type":"tool_result","content":"499\texport type PeekExportResult = {\n500\t  filename: string;\n501\t  rowCount: number;\n502\t  rowCap: number;\n503\t  rowCapApplied: boolean;\n504\t  columns: ReadonlyArray<PeekTableColumn>;\n505\t  rows: ReadonlyArray<PeekExportRow>;\n506\t};\n507\t\n508\t// --- Universal search (FR-5) -------------------------------------------------\n509\t//\n510\t// One search entry point that resolves common operational identifiers to typed\n511\t// result groups. Results are grouped by entity type so the UI can section them\n512\t// (user, referral, linked account, round, transaction, queue event). Each\n513\t// result includes enough context to disambiguate similar matches; sensitive\n514\t// values (wallet, Telegram id, tx signature) live in the result's `id`/`label`\n515\t// fields for operator readability and the audit event records only the actor\n516\t// email, query class, and result counts (never the raw query, which the audit\n517\t// writer redacts if it looks like a secret).\n518\t\n519\texport type PeekSearchEntityType =\n520\t  | \"user\"\n521\t  | \"referral\"\n522\t  | \"linked_account\"\n523\t  | \"round\"\n524\t  | \"transaction\"\n525\t  | \"queue_event\";\n526\t\n527\texport const PEEK_SEARCH_ENTITY_TYPES: ReadonlyArray<PeekSearchEntityType> = [\n528\t  \"user\",\n529\t  \"referral\",\n530\t  \"linked_account\",\n531\t  \"round\",\n532\t  \"transaction\",\n533\t  \"queue_event\",\n534\t];\n535\t\n536\t// Coarse heuristic classification used only for the `peek.search` audit\n537\t// summary so reviewers can see which class of identifier was searched without\n538\t// inferring it from the (possibly redacted) raw query.\n539\texport type PeekSearchQueryClass =\n540\t  | \"empty\"\n541\t  | \"free_text\"\n542\t  | \"user_id\"\n543\t  | \"username\"\n544\t  | \"wallet\"\n545\t  | \"referral_code\"\n546\t  | \"telegram_username\"\n547\t  | \"telegram_provider_id\"\n548\t  | \"round_pda\"\n549\t  | \"match_id\"\n550\t  | \"tx_signature\"\n551\t  | \"queue_event_id\";\n552\t\n553\texport type PeekSearchResult = {\n554\t  entityType: PeekSearchEntityType;\n555\t  id: string;\n556\t  label: string;\n557\t  sublabel: string | null;\n558\t  context: string | null;\n559\t  href: string;\n560\t};\n561\t\n562\texport type PeekSearchGroup = {\n563\t  entityType: PeekSearchEntityType;\n564\t  results: ReadonlyArray<PeekSearchResult>;\n565\t  truncated: boolean;\n566\t};\n567\t\n568\texport type PeekSearchResponse = {\n569\t  query: string;\n570\t  queryClass: PeekSearchQueryClass;\n571\t  groups: ReadonlyArray<PeekSearchGroup>;\n572\t  totalResults: number;\n573\t  perGroupLimit: number;\n574\t  generatedAt: string;\n575\t};\n576\t\n577\texport const PEEK_SEARCH_DEFAULT_PER_GROUP_LIMIT = 5;\n578\texport const PEEK_SEARCH_MAX_PER_GROUP_LIMIT = 25;\n579\t\n580\t// --- Growth + referral admin (FR-7) ------------------------------------------\n581\t//\n582\t// Browser-safe view models for `/growth/referrals` and `/growth/kol`. The\n583\t// engine queries surface (a) overview metrics that fit the FR-4 metric\n584\t// bookkeeping, (b) top-referrer rows that combine `referral_links`,\n585\t// `referral_codes`, `referral_earnings`, and pending `referral_claims` per\n586\t// referrer, (c) KOL rows that join `referral_kol_rates` with linked\n587\t// performance from `referral_links`/`referral_earnings`, (d) claim rows for\n588\t// the filterable `/growth/referrals` claims table, and (e) a one-hop\n589\t// referral-graph node that lets the UI navigate from a user-detail page to\n590\t// the inbound referrer or any outbound referee and back.\n591\t//\n592\t// All numeric/precision-sensitive values arrive as `text` to preserve u64\n593\t// lamport precision; the UI formats at render time.\n594\t\n595\texport type PeekGrowthOverviewMetricId =\n596\t  | \"growth.referrers\"\n597\t  | \"growth.referred_users\"\n598\t  | \"growth.activated_referred_users\""}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"242d752c-50cc-49e1-a8d0-306af8621059","uuid":"92b36cf3-22cd-4ab2-a1a2-1a95bac0f173","timestamp":"2026-04-26T15:06:36.778Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/src/lib/types/peek.ts","content":"export type PeekExportResult = {\n  filename: string;\n  rowCount: number;\n  rowCap: number;\n  rowCapApplied: boolean;\n  columns: ReadonlyArray<PeekTableColumn>;\n  rows: ReadonlyArray<PeekExportRow>;\n};\n\n// --- Universal search (FR-5) -------------------------------------------------\n//\n// One search entry point that resolves common operational identifiers to typed\n// result groups. Results are grouped by entity type so the UI can section them\n// (user, referral, linked account, round, transaction, queue event). Each\n// result includes enough context to disambiguate similar matches; sensitive\n// values (wallet, Telegram id, tx signature) live in the result's `id`/`label`\n// fields for operator readability and the audit event records only the actor\n// email, query class, and result counts (never the raw query, which the audit\n// writer redacts if it looks like a secret).\n\nexport type PeekSearchEntityType =\n  | \"user\"\n  | \"referral\"\n  | \"linked_account\"\n  | \"round\"\n  | \"transaction\"\n  | \"queue_event\";\n\nexport const PEEK_SEARCH_ENTITY_TYPES: ReadonlyArray<PeekSearchEntityType> = [\n  \"user\",\n  \"referral\",\n  \"linked_account\",\n  \"round\",\n  \"transaction\",\n  \"queue_event\",\n];\n\n// Coarse heuristic classification used only for the `peek.search` audit\n// summary so reviewers can see which class of identifier was searched without\n// inferring it from the (possibly redacted) raw query.\nexport type PeekSearchQueryClass =\n  | \"empty\"\n  | \"free_text\"\n  | \"user_id\"\n  | \"username\"\n  | \"wallet\"\n  | \"referral_code\"\n  | \"telegram_username\"\n  | \"telegram_provider_id\"\n  | \"round_pda\"\n  | \"match_id\"\n  | \"tx_signature\"\n  | \"queue_event_id\";\n\nexport type PeekSearchResult = {\n  entityType: PeekSearchEntityType;\n  id: string;\n  label: string;\n  sublabel: string | null;\n  context: string | null;\n  href: string;\n};\n\nexport type PeekSearchGroup = {\n  entityType: PeekSearchEntityType;\n  results: ReadonlyArray<PeekSearchResult>;\n  truncated: boolean;\n};\n\nexport type PeekSearchResponse = {\n  query: string;\n  queryClass: PeekSearchQueryClass;\n  groups: ReadonlyArray<PeekSearchGroup>;\n  totalResults: number;\n  perGroupLimit: number;\n  generatedAt: string;\n};\n\nexport const PEEK_SEARCH_DEFAULT_PER_GROUP_LIMIT = 5;\nexport const PEEK_SEARCH_MAX_PER_GROUP_LIMIT = 25;\n\n// --- Growth + referral admin (FR-7) ------------------------------------------\n//\n// Browser-safe view models for `/growth/referrals` and `/growth/kol`. The\n// engine queries surface (a) overview metrics that fit the FR-4 metric\n// bookkeeping, (b) top-referrer rows that combine `referral_links`,\n// `referral_codes`, `referral_earnings`, and pending `referral_claims` per\n// referrer, (c) KOL rows that join `referral_kol_rates` with linked\n// performance from `referral_links`/`referral_earnings`, (d) claim rows for\n// the filterable `/growth/referrals` claims table, and (e) a one-hop\n// referral-graph node that lets the UI navigate from a user-detail page to\n// the inbound referrer or any outbound referee and back.\n//\n// All numeric/precision-sensitive values arrive as `text` to preserve u64\n// lamport precision; the UI formats at render time.\n\nexport type PeekGrowthOverviewMetricId =\n  | \"growth.referrers\"\n  | \"growth.referred_users\"\n  | \"growth.activated_referred_users\"","numLines":100,"startLine":499,"totalLines":1476}}}
